text.section:
The successor shall file with the Department:
A property certificate under § 3-112 of this article or § 10-208(h) of this title, or both; and
A certificate that specifies:
Each county in the State where a foreign limited partnership party to the merger, except the successor, owned an interest in land;
The name of each party to the merger;
The place under the laws of which each party was organized;
The name of the successor; and
If the successor is a foreign limited partnership, or foreign partnership, the name and business, residence, or mailing address of each of the general partners of the successor.
The certificate shall be executed:
In the case of a partnership, in the manner required in § 9A-903 of this article;
In the case of a limited partnership, by all of the general partners;
In the case of a limited liability company in the manner required in § 4A-206 of this article; and
In the case of a corporation or business trust, in the manner required by Title 1 of this article.
